            <p>
                Infosys Limited is a global leader in technology services and consulting, headquartered in Bangalore, India. Founded in 1981 by a group of seven engineers including Narayana Murthy, Nandan Nilekani, S. Gopalakrishnan (Kris), S.D. Shibulal, K. Dinesh, Ashok Arora, and N.S. Raghavan, the company was established with an initial capital of â‚¹10,000. Narayana Murthy played a pivotal role in setting the foundation for Infosys, which has grown into one of the largest IT services companies globally.
            </p>
            As of 2024, Salil Parekh serves as the Chief Executive Officer (CEO) and Managing Director. Parekh, who took over in January 2018, has been instrumental in driving Infosys' strategic direction, particularly focusing on digital transformation and cloud services.

            <p>
                Infosys specializes in a wide range of services, including IT consulting, software development, business process outsourcing, and digital transformation. The company serves clients across diverse industries such as financial services, manufacturing, healthcare, retail, and telecommunications. It is particularly known for its flagship service delivery model, Global Delivery Model, which emphasizes cost efficiency and resource optimization by distributing work globally.
            </p>
            <p>
                A publicly traded company, Infosys is listed on the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE), the National Stock Exchange (NSE) in India, and the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) in the United States. It became the first Indian company to list on NASDAQ in 1999.Infosys has been a pioneer in innovation and sustainability, emphasizing a culture of learning and inclusivity. The company has invested heavily in research and development, establishing Infosys Labs to foster innovation in emerging technologies such as artificial intelligence, blockchain, and IoT.  
            </p>
            <p>
                The company operates in over 50 countries, employing more than 350,000 employees globally. Its training campus in Mysore is one of the largest corporate training facilities in the world.

               In addition to its business achievements, Infosys is known for its strong focus on corporate social responsibility (CSR) through the Infosys Foundation, which engages in initiatives related to education, healthcare, and rural development.

               Infosys has consistently ranked among the top global IT services providers and is recognized for its ethical business practices, sustainability efforts, and emphasis on employee welfare. It continues to shape the digital future of businesses worldwide, aligning with its mission of "navigating your next."
            </p>
            
